cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SI

This paper deals with the problem of detecting infected computers by analyzing their network traffic. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as machine learning (cs.LG) since the proposed solution involves a discriminative model implemented as a neural network. The use of network sensors such as proxy servers and firewalls also suggests a sub-category of network and internet security (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper mentions the automatic learning of server types, which could fall under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
